==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-interrupt.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
'''to interrupt''' ('''interrupts''', '''interrupted''', '''interrupting''')

# to [[disturb]] or [[halt]] an [[ongoing]] [[process]] or [[action]] by [[interfere|interfering]] [[sudden]]ly
#:''A maverick politician repeatedly '''interrupted''' the debate by shouting.''
# (''computing'') To assert to a [[computer]] that an exceptional condition must be handled.
#:''The [[packet]] receiver circuit '''interrupted''' the microprocessor.''

====Synonyms====
#[[continue]], [[resume]]

====Derived terms====
*[[interruption]]

====Translations====
*German: [[unterbrechen]] (1)
*Spanish: [[interrumpir]]
*Telugu: [[అడ్డుకొను]] (aDDukonu)

===Noun===
'''interrupt''' ([[interrupts]])

# (''computing'') An event that causes a computer to temporarily cease what it was doing and attend to a condition
#: ''The '''interrupt''' caused the packet handler routine to run.''

